name: Biscuit
description: Stopmotion program created by the members of Bricks in Motion a Lego stopmotion community as an alternative to paid applications this is by brickfilmers for brickfilmers. http://bricksinmotion.com

scripts.build: npm run clean && npm run build:osx && npm run build:win
scripts.pack: npm run pack:osx && npm run pack:win

releases.name: Biscuit Version 1.1.1
releases.body: Fixed problems where Biscuit would not load.

releases.name: Biscuit Version 1.1
releases.body:
Cleaning up.
Smoother transitions, better buttons, better formatting.
Dynamic window resizing.
Controls (not draggable yet)
    - Change aspect ratio of camera frame capture

releases.name: Biscuit Version 1.0
releases.body:
Adds exporting to video.

Not tested on Windows.
CONFIRMED NOT WORKING ON WINDOWS.
MAY BE WORKING! PLEASE GIVE FEEDBACK!
I NEED PEOPLE TO TEST WINDOWS! PLEASE TEST AND POST FEEDBACK!
Will be fixed very soon.

releases.name: Biscuit Version 0.5.0
releases.body:
Added shortcuts
CTRL/CMD + C [go to camera]
CTRL/CMD + H [go to home]
CTRL/CMD + A [go to audio]
CTRL/CMD + W [go to write]
R [take a frame]
P [start playback]

releases.name: Biscuit Version 0.3.0
releases.body: Added audio recording, ability to scroll down to view all frames.

releases.name: Biscuit Version 0.2.1
releases.body:
Fixed issues when extracting on windows. 
Speed improvements.

releases.name: Biscuit Version 0.2.0
releases.body: Added playback.  Fixed some minor issues.

releases.name: Biscuit Version 0.1.0
releases.body:
Togglable onion skinning.  Can actually be used (so version changed to 0.1).
No longer alpha.

releases.name: Biscuit Alpha 0.0.2
releases.body:
Biscuit alpha release 0.0.2.  This version saves all taken frames, but will overwrite frames already in the directory.
As this version does save all frames, it is suitable for actual use.

releases.name: Biscuit Alpha 0.0.1
releases.body: This is the first alpha release of Biscuit, this is only meant for testing not for actual use.  Currently the program only saves the first frame taken, so please do not use this for actual use.
